Subtitle of Senate Bill 406
TO REQUIRE A COUNTY RECORDER TO VERIFY CERTAIN INFORMATION BEFORE
RECORDING A DEED TO REAL ESTATE.
______________________________________________________________________
Amendment No. 3 to Senate Bill 406
Amend Senate Bill 406 as engrossed S3/19/25 (version: 3/19/25 02:22:22 PM):
Page 1, line 25, delete "(f)(1)(A)" and substitute "(f)(1)(A)(i)"
AND
Page 1, delete line 27, and substitute the following:
"recorder unless the grantor named in the deed to real estate or an
individual signing the deed on behalf of the grantor named in the deed to
real estate"
AND
Page 1, delete line 29, and substitute the following:
"identification card or driver's license.
(ii) If a deed to real estate is presented to a
recorder for recording by mail, the grantor named in the deed to the real
estate shall include a photocopy of his or her valid photo identification or
driver's license with the deed to real estate submitted by mail."
AND
Page 1, line 34, delete "(C)(i)" and substitute "(C)"
